Behavior contract (per H.6 spec):
  ✓ memory 256→512 MB: 2× CPU allocation (Lambda CPU scales
    proportionally with memory).
  ✓ reservedConcurrentExecutions=10: caps the EB-tick + H.4 chain
    + parallel-overlap worst case at 10 simultaneous Lambdas. Above
    that, additional invocations get throttled by Lambda (which is
    fine — next EB tick picks them up).
  ✓ EMF metrics: 7 metrics per sweep (scanned, dispatched, paused,
    failed, throttled, duration_ms, chain_depth) emitted as a
    single JSON log line. No PutMetricData call; CloudWatch Logs
    automatically extracts via the _aws envelope.
  ✓ CloudWatchMetricAlarm BasicsCronKickerFailedAlarm: fires when
    Sum(failed) > 10 over 5 minutes. Catches adapter regressions
    + Composio outages + workspace-level connectivity loss.
  ✓ CloudWatchMetricAlarm BasicsCronKickerDurationAlarm: fires
    when Maximum(duration_ms) > 240000 (80% of the 5-min Lambda
    timeout). Catches slow adapters or DB pool latency before
    Lambda kills the invocation.

Static checks:
