  ✓ pnpm -F @basics/worker exec tsc --noEmit  clean

Adversarial review: skipped (kind: infra per spec).

Notes / decisions:
  - SST's sst.aws.Function exposes `concurrency: { reserved: N }`
    as a clean abstraction over pulumi's reservedConcurrentExecutions.
  - EMF emission is one console.log call per sweep — no
    aws-sdk/client-cloudwatch dependency added (which would have
    blown up the kicker bundle). CloudWatch Logs subscribes to
    Lambda's stdout already.
  - Dimensions: [[]] (empty dimension set) emits the metric without
    any dimension — suitable for the kicker's "global per-tick"
    counts. Future work could add per-workspace dimensions if
    operator wants per-workspace dashboards.
  - Duration threshold 240s = 80% of Lambda's 5-min timeout —
    leaves headroom for the operator to investigate before the
    Lambda is killed mid-sweep.

